<HEADLINE>
<P>
AYATOLLAH KHOMEINI AND 'THE SATANIC VERSES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I've got my order in for a copy of "The Satanic Verses" and I'm pleased to say 
my bookseller tells me there is a long list of waiting buyers. 
</P>
<P>
I'll wait. It was 30-odd years before I finally got around to reading "The Last 
Temptation of Christ" and what a wonderful discovery it was. It taught me more 
about the profound meaning of Christ the man and myth than all the turgid 
sermons I ever heard before I finally gave up looking for any sense or 
spirituality in churches as a young man. 
</P>
<P>
I eagerly look forward to learning something about Islam that isn't filtered 
through the twisted megalomania of a power-mad old imam or, even worse, through 
the self-righteous "moderate" high priests who don't necessarily want to kill 
the author but would stop any of us from making our own choices by banning the 
book. 
</P>
<P>
And by the way, shame on those booksellers who so quickly ducked their heads in 
the sand. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH GALE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
