<HEADLINE>
<P>
AYATOLLAH KHOMEINI AND 'THE SATANIC VERSES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The death threat by Iranian leaders against a British author, plus the sizable 
bounty to murder the writer, represents a serious challenge to Muslim leaders 
throughout the world. They have a choice to renounce this vicious example of 
terrorism or to remain silent and give the impression that such despotism is 
not inconsistent with Islam. 
</P>
<P>
Political democracies, especially Britain and the United States, are also 
challenged. Are they willing to permit interference with the artistic freedom 
of expression that has played such a central role in Western civilization? Our 
recent history suggests that such attacks on our basic values should not be 
ignored. 
</P>
<P>
HOWARD H. KENDLER 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara 
</P>
</TEXT>
