<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S VIETNAM MEMORIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a World War II front-line nurse in the admittance tent of an evacuation 
hospital in Europe, I have tried for many years to get Colorado congressmen to 
support a statue of the World War II combat nurses to no avail. Nurses 
volunteered, we were not drafted. Many men would have died if they had not 
received front-line care. 
</P>
<P>
The nurses on Corregidor suffered the most. I saw some at Fort Dix when they 
returned. I'll never forget the faces of these young women. Faces of wounded 
and dead servicemen still are in my mind after 44 years. We all suffered shock. 
</P>
<P>
Nurses deserve a statue for service in any war that a man has a statue erected 
to him. We helped to preserve democracy. 
</P>
<P>
ISABELLE P. DEXTER 
</P>
<P>
Arvada, Colo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
