<HEADLINE>
<P>
PADRES SHOULD PLAY AL OPPONENTS, TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clearly a unique team sport and acknowledged as America's pastime, I find major 
league baseball lacking an obvious dimension -- regular-season inter-league 
play. 
</P>
<P>
Baseball's "weaker sisters" (NBA, NFL, NHL) all seem to understand its appeal, 
but I've yet to see baseball address the issue, or for that matter, find the 
media discussing the topic. In lieu of the same old schedule, the Padres could 
add a home-and-home series with each American League team. Wow! Could you 
imagine all those American League teams in town? The 162-game season would 
still be honored but simply adjusted to accommodate its new personality. 
</P>
<P>
Clearly, the fans would love it, and consequently the owners would benefit from 
the increased attendance. 
</P>
<P>
TONY BRADA 
</P>
<P>
Carlsbad 
</P>
</TEXT>
