<HEADLINE>
<P>
BISHOP'S WINS 1-A SOCCER WITH 1-0 OVERTIME VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Josh Parks, a sophomore midfielder, scored from six yards with 5 minutes left 
in overtime to give The Bishop's School (15-4-3) a 1-0 victory over the 
Army-Navy Academy (11-4-3) Friday in the San Diego Section 1-A boys' soccer 
championship match at San Diego High School. 
</P>
<P>
The schools had split two matches during the regular season and were scoreless 
after 85 minutes of play Friday until Phillip Button passed to Charlie 
Marshall, whose shot from 13 feet was deflected by the Army-Navy goalie. 
</P>
<P>
Button took the deflection and, with his back to the goal, passed left to 
Parks, who scored the winning goal. 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
Division 2-A quarterfinals 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 3, Mission Bay 0 -- Derek Berry scored two goals as top-seeded 
Valhalla (23-0-0) scored all its goals in the second half. Valhalla recorded 
its 17th shutout. Mission Bay finished 12-5-5. 
</P>
<P>
University City 2, Ramona 1 -- Mike O'Shea and Kevin Fay each scored for 
University City (16-3-3). Ramona finished 19-3-2. 
</P>
<P>
San Marcos 3, Crawford 0 -- Joel Neri scored two goals for San Marcos (15-4-3). 
Victor Chavez added the third goal. Crawford finished 17-7-1. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 3, Carlsbad 0 -- Manny Rodriquez, Jose Pulido and Gaing Lai each 
scored for San Diego (17-1-2). Carlsbad finished 14-7-2. 
</P>
<P>
Girls 
</P>
<P>
Division 2-A quarterfinals 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont 1, Christian 0 -- Left forward Jennifer Strauss scored 2 minutes into 
the second half for Grossmont (14-3-5). Tara Tamber had 16 saves for Christian 
(9-6-3). 
</P>
<P>
Valhalla 3, San Marcos 0 -- Kerri Williams scored two goals assisted by Terry 
Veisel for Valhalla (19-4-2). Peggy Pollem scored Valhalla's third goal. April 
Austin had nine saves for San Marcos (16-9-1). 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 3, University City 1 -- San Pasqual led 3-0 after the first half as 
the top-seeded team advanced to the semifinals. Sisters Suzie and Stacy 
Esposito scored a goal apiece and Heather Armstrong added a goal for San 
Pasqual (23-1-2). University City finished 17-3-1. 
</P>
<P>
Ramona 2, USDHS 0 -- Isabel Diaz and Nicole Curtis each scored one goal for 
Ramona (22-2-1). Crutis was assisted by Kristi Smoyer. USDHS finished 12-3-3. 
</P>
