<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE, SMOKE BLAMED ON POWER FAILURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A power failure Friday morning at the Fletcher Oil refinery in Carson produced 
large flames and a billowing cloud of black smoke that was visible for miles. 
</P>
<P>
Company Vice President Richard D. Erdman said the power outage knocked out 
controls on a refinery unit and excess gases were burned off through a flare, 
sending flames soaring 80 to 90 feet into the air. "It was rather spectacular 
because it went straight up," Erdman said. 
</P>
<P>
The 10-minute outage was caused by a battery failure in "a very critical piece 
of equipment" designed to supply uninterrupted power, he said. 
</P>
<P>
A South Coast Air Quality Management District spokesman said the refinery will 
not be cited for violating air pollution laws because the smoke was the result 
of "a legitimate breakdown." 
</P>
</TEXT>
