<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For a team that seemed to have all the answers, UC Irvine staggered out of 
Thursday night's loss to Cal State Long Beach with a lot of questions. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters (11-13, 8-7 in the Big West) had just one day to regroup. They 
will play New Mexico State (17-8, 10-5) at 5 p.m. today at the Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
New Mexico State dominated Irvine in the teams' first meeting, 90-69. The 
Aggies' front line of Johnny Roberson, Willie Joseph and center James Anderson 
made a combined 23 of 37 shots and scored 54 points in that game. JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022589-0062 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 23202 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
