<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part 3; Page 4; Column 5; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
98 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NELSON SCORES 35 TO LEAD TROJANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Center Cherie Nelson scored 35 points to lead the USC women's basketball team 
over Washington State, 87-67, Friday night in a Pacific 10 game at USC's North 
Gym. 
</P>
<P>
Tammy Hammond scored 16 points for the Trojans (10-14 overall and 6-8 in the 
Pac-10), and Tammy Story had 14 points, six assists and six steals. For the 
Cougars (12-13, 5-10), Angie Miller had 16 points and nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Washington 64, UCLA 62 -- Despite career highs of 32 points and 18 rebounds by 
UCLA's Sandra VanEmbricqs, the Bruins (11-13, 7-7) lost to the Huskies (19-9, 
12-3) in a Pac-10 game at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
