</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An announcement of the sale of the Dallas Cowboys could be made as early as 
today, a spokesman for the National Football League franchise said Friday, as 
speculation surrounding Coach Tom Landry's future with the organization 
intensified. 
</P>
<P>
H.R. (Bum) Bright, majority owner of the team, met for much of the day with 
Arkansas oilman Jerry Jones, who the Miami Herald said had worked out a deal to 
buy the team for $180 million. 
</P>
<P>
