<HEADLINE>
<P>
REBEL GOVERNMENT WILL PROLONG CIVIL WAR, KABUL SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KABUL, Afghanistan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Afghan Foreign Ministry on Friday dismissed the election of a rebel 
government in exile as a Pakistani-orchestrated exercise that will prolong the 
civil war. 
</P>
<P>
"(It) will have no other results than the continuation of bloodshed," a 
ministry spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The Afghan rebels, based in Pakistan, launched their new exile government 
Friday by demanding Afghanistan's seat at the United Nations and calling on 
supporters of the Kabul government of President Najibullah to desert it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
