MARINE KILLED WHEN CAR ROLLS IN OCEANSIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old Marine was killed Friday afternoon after he lost control of his 
car on North River Road in Oceanside, police said. 
</P>
<P>
An initial investigation by the Oceanside Police Department indicated that the 
man was driving west when he lost control of the car, which ran off the road 
and overturned. 
</P>
<P>
The driver was thrown from the car as it rolled, and the vehicle landed on top 
of him. He was pronounced dead at the scene. There were no passengers. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation was continuing Friday night, and the victim's name was being 
withheld pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
