<P>
Photo, He Delivers Love With GroceriesWhen Nate Boinus drops off groceries to 
San Fernando Valley senior citizens such as Jean Dotson, below, he doesn't just 
bring produce and canned goods. He also brings contact with the outside world. 
"A lot of them never see anybody," said Boinus, 81, who works for a senior 
outreach program. "I'm the only one they ever see." Shopping means whizzing 
down aisles with two carts, and Boinus makes enough deliveries to fill a van. 
He thinks the work helps keep him fit. "I see too many people younger than me 
spending too much time with the shades drawn, watching TV," he said. "They look 
three times my age . . .. More people should get out of the house and do 
things." ROBERT DURELL / Los Angeles Times 
