<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO DRUG CENTER IN LAKE VIEW TERRACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Iam opposed to the planned Phoenix House/Nancy Reagan Center's being located in 
Lake View Terrace. 
</P>
<P>
As a resident of Lake View Terrace, I am familiar with the proposed site and 
think that far more suitable locations are available elsewhere. The site in 
question, a former medical center, is surrounded by single-family homes and has 
two schools nearby. 
</P>
<P>
I realize the Valley needs such a facility. However, it is time another 
community assumes this responsibility. Lake View Terrace already contains 
several facilities for the treatment of drug and alcohol abuse, a sanitarium 
for the mentally ill, a youth correctional facility and the Lopez Canyon 
Landfill, which accepts the majority of L.A.'s trash. OUR BACK YARD IS ALREADY 
FULL! IT'S SOMEONE ELSE'S TURN! 
</P>
<P>
THOMAS D. FAY 
</P>
<P>
Lake View Terrace 
</P>
</TEXT>
