<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE COLLEGES; 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CHAPMAN'S BIRD SHUTS OUT POMONA, 2-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Bird pitched a 6-hitter and Chapman College defeated Cal Poly Pomona, 
2-0, Friday in the California Collegiate Athletic Assn. baseball opener for 
both teams at Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
Bird (2-3), a former Sonora High School standout, struck out six and walked 
one. 
</P>
<P>
Chapman (7-7 overall) took a 1-0 lead in the first on an unearned run. 
</P>
<P>
David Allison walked and reached second on a fielder's choice. Kenny Briggs 
then hit a ground ball that went through the legs of second baseman Miccal 
Jackson. Allison scored on the play. 
</P>
<P>
The score remained 1-0 until the ninth, when the Panthers' Jeff Kidwiler 
doubled home Jody Garcia. Kidwiler had two hits in the game. 
</P>
<P>
Brett Lachemann took the loss, although he gave up just five hits in 7 2/3 
innings. He struck out five and allowed only the unearned run. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara 6, Southern California College 1 -- Joe Aversa (2-1) went nine 
innings but took the loss for visiting SCC (6-4). UC Santa Barbara is 8-7. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 3-1, San Diego State 2-0 -- Laura Papadakis singled home Shelly Mahon 
with two outs in the ninth to give Chapman (6-2) the victory in the first game, 
which went nine innings. Jacki Blake (2-1) threw a two-hitter, striking out 
nine, for the victory in the second game. 
</P>
<P>
In the National Indoor Team Tennis Championships in Louisville, Ky.: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 5, USC 4 -- With the score tied, 4-4, Irvine's No. 1 doubles of Mike 
Briggs and Trevor Kronemann rallied to defeat Kent Seton and Murphy Jensen, 
3-6, 7-5, 7-6, for the Anteaters (4-4) in a quarterfinal match. Briggs and 
Kronemann trailed, 4-3, in the second set, but broke service to pull even. 
Kronemann also defeated Byron Black, 6-3, 7-6. The Anteaters will play the 
University of South Carolina today in the semifinals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
