<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST : LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
'STU FINE FIELD' TO BE DEDICATED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newport-Mesa Unified School District officials today will formally name the 
varsity baseball playing area at Newport Harbor High School for Stuart W. Fine, 
a parent and longtime volunteer umpire who died last year. 
</P>
<P>
Noon ceremonies at the school will designate the baseball area as "Stu Fine 
Field." Fine, a Newport Beach real estate broker and former teacher, died Jan. 
24, 1988, of a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
Fine, a former varsity baseball player for Pepperdine University, spent much of 
his spare time as a volunteer coach and umpire for the Newport National Little 
League, the Boys Club of the Harbor Area and Newport Harbor High. 
</P>
<P>
After graduating from Pepperdine in 1959, Fine was a junior high teacher in 
Bishop and Tustin. He entered the real estate business in 1963. 
</P>
<P>
Fine's wife, Esther, said she is pleased and proud that her husband's memory is 
being honored by the high school. "This would have meant so much to him," she 
said. "Baseball and youth were his loves." 
</P>
</TEXT>
